{
  "text": "The Design Repository schema is built on a PostgreSQL database [CITATION_1] . The schema is divided into sections representing seven types of information: artifact-, function-, failure-, physical-, performance-, sensory-and media-related information. Artifact hierarchy is developed by using a parent-child relationship in the artifact table [CITATION_2] . These tables provides information regarding the artifacts in terms of their names, type of assembly, quantity, corresponding component basis system name, input flow, and output flow.",
  "citation_candidates": [
